1.10	Al-Zawiya,_Khirbat	Zawiya, Khirbat	Al-Zawiya (Arabic: ‎) was a Palestinian Arab village in the District of Baysan. It was depopulated by the Israel Defence Force during the 1948 Arab-Israeli War on May 15–18, 1948 under Operation Gideon. It was located 11.5 km northeast of Baysan. The Crusader Castle Belvoir is located close to the village.	
